---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import FeatureCard from '../components/FeatureCard.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Attorney Buyer Representation Sonoma County | Legal Protection at 1% Commission"
  description="Comprehensive buyer representation with legal precision. Property search, contract negotiation, due diligence, and closing support at just 1% commission."
  keywords="attorney buyer representation Sonoma County, real estate attorney contract review home purchase, exclusive buyer agent no conflict of interest Sonoma, attorney due diligence rural property Sonoma County, buy home Sonoma County legal help, attorney broker wine country property purchase"
>
    <section style="margin-top: 120px;">
        <h1 class="section-title">Buyer Representation Services in Sonoma County</h1>
        <p class="section-subtitle">Comprehensive buyer representation with legal precision.</p>

        <div class="features">
            <FeatureCard
                icon="🔍"
                title="Property Search"
                description="Access to all MLS listings and off-market opportunities. We help you identify properties that meet your criteria and budget, with honest assessments of value and potential."
            />
            <FeatureCard
                icon="📋"
                title="Contract Negotiation"
                description="Strategic offer preparation and negotiation. Our legal background ensures every term protects your interests, from price to contingencies to closing timeline."
            />
            <FeatureCard
                icon="🔐"
                title="Due Diligence"
                description="Thorough review of inspections, disclosures, and title. We identify red flags and ensure you understand exactly what you're buying before you commit."
            />
            <FeatureCard
                icon="📄"
                title="Contract Review"
                description="Line-by-line analysis of all purchase documents. We explain complex legal language in plain English and protect you from unfavorable terms or hidden obligations."
            />
            <FeatureCard
                icon="🤝"
                title="Closing Support"
                description="Guidance through escrow, final walkthroughs, and closing. We coordinate with lenders, escrow officers, and sellers to ensure a smooth transaction from contract to keys."
            />
            <FeatureCard
                icon="💡"
                title="Market Analysis"
                description="Data-driven insights on pricing, trends, and comparable sales. Make informed decisions backed by current market data and our deep local knowledge."
            />
        </div>

        <div style="margin-top: 4rem; padding: 3rem; background: var(--cream); border-radius: 4px;">
            <h2 style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 2rem; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 1rem;">What a Regular Agent Cannot Do — But an Attorney-Broker Can</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-light); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 2rem;">Most buyer's agents are skilled at finding properties and writing offers. But when contract language is ambiguous, when a disclosure raises a legal question, or when a seller's demand creates potential liability, a standard agent has to say: <em>"You should probably talk to a lawyer."</em></p>
            <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem;">
                <div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Spot Contract Language That Costs You</h3>
                    <p style="color: var(--text-light); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.8;">Attorney-level contract review catches vague indemnification clauses, unfavorable AS-IS provisions, and seller carve-outs that can shift repair costs onto you after closing.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Legal Due Diligence on Rural & Vineyard Properties</h3>
                    <p style="color: var(--text-light); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.8;">Buying agricultural land or a Sonoma County vineyard? Water rights, PTRA well ordinances, easements, and zoning restrictions require legal analysis — not just a property inspection.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Interpret Disclosures Without Guessing</h3>
                    <p style="color: var(--text-light); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.8;">California sellers are required to disclose material defects, but what they disclose — and how they word it — has legal consequences. We read disclosures as lawyers, not just agents.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Negotiate With Legal Leverage</h3>
                    <p style="color: var(--text-light); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.8;">Knowing the law changes how you negotiate. When a seller's response to your repair request is legally questionable, an attorney-broker can press back with authority.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-top: 2rem; padding: 3rem; background: var(--white); border-radius: 4px; box-shadow: 0 4px 30px var(--shadow);">
            <h3 style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 2rem; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">What's Included</h3>
            <ul style="list-style: none; color: var(--text-light); line-height: 2.2; font-size: 1.05rem;">
                <li>✓ Full buyer representation throughout the transaction</li>
                <li>✓ MLS access and property search assistance</li>
                <li>✓ Property showings and area tours</li>
                <li>✓ Comparative market analysis for each property</li>
                <li>✓ Offer preparation and strategic negotiation</li>
                <li>✓ Contract review and explanation</li>
                <li>✓ Coordination with inspectors, lenders, and escrow</li>
                <li>✓ Review of all disclosures and reports</li>
                <li>✓ Guidance through contingency periods</li>
                <li>✓ Final walkthrough coordination</li>
                <li>✓ Closing assistance and documentation review</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>
